# Typography

## Font stack (approved fonts loaded in `index.html`)

| Role | Font | Tailwind class | When to use |
|------|------|---------------|-------------|
| Display / headings | **Syne** | `font-[Syne]` | Hero, page titles, section headings, sidebar brand, buttons (landing) |
| Accent / editorial | **Newsreader** | `font-['Newsreader']` | Single-word emphasis inside headings, italic flourish |
| UI body / labels | **DM Sans** | `font-['DM_Sans']` | Badges, captions, small-caps labels, body paragraphs |
| Body (alt) | **Outfit** | `font-['Outfit']` | Longer form content, dashboard body text |
| Serif accent | **Instrument Serif** | `font-['Instrument_Serif']` | Decorative use only |

Do **not** add new font families without updating `index.html` and this rule.
Never fall back to Inter, Roboto, Arial, or system-ui as a primary.

## Type scale

| Element | Classes | Example |
|---------|---------|---------|
| Page title (H1) | `text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight` | Dashboard pages, settings |
| Hero heading | `font-[Syne] text-[clamp(3rem,8vw,6.5rem)] font-bold tracking-[-0.04em] leading-[0.95] text-balance` | Landing hero |
| Section heading (H2) | `font-[Syne] text-[clamp(2rem,5vw,3.5rem)] font-bold tracking-tight leading-tight` | Landing sections |
| Dashboard section (H2) | `text-base font-semibold` | Settings panels |
| Card title | `text-base font-semibold leading-snug tracking-tight` | Alert titles, card headers |
| Body | `text-sm` | Default prose |
| Caption / secondary | `text-xs text-muted-foreground` | Metadata, timestamps |
| Badge / label | `font-['DM_Sans'] text-[11px] uppercase tracking-[0.18em] font-medium` | Landing badges |

Maintain heading hierarchy: `<h1>` → `<h2>` → `<h3>`. Never skip levels.

## Text conventions

- Ellipsis: `…` (U+2026), never `...`
- Curly quotes: `"` `"` not straight `"`
- Loading states: end with `…` — "Loading…", "Saving…", "Redirecting…"
- Non-breaking space for units: `10&nbsp;MB`, `⌘&nbsp;K`
- Number columns: add `tabular-nums` for alignment
- Multi-line headings: prefer `text-balance` or `text-pretty` to prevent widows
- Button labels: Title Case, specific verbs ("Save API Key" not "Continue")
- Error messages: include a fix or next step, not just the problem
